210 "§40-23-40
211 (a) On June 15, 2023, the definition of "food" in
212 Sections 40-23-1 and 40-23-60 shall apply to county and
213 municipal sales and use taxes. For purposes of county and
214 municipal sales and use taxes, the sales tax rate on food
215 shall be established as the general or retail sales tax rate
216 in effect in the county or municipality on June 15, 2023,
217 unless otherwise provided by law. An act of the Legislature or
218 an ordinance or resolution adopted by a county or municipal
219 governing body levying a county or municipal sales and use tax
220 inclusive of food passed or enacted on or before June 15,
221 2023, shall remain operative, but no additional county or
222 municipal sales and use taxes on food may be levied.
223 (b) Any county or municipal governing body, by
224 resolution or ordinance, may reduce the general or retail
Page 8

resolution or ordinance, may reduce the general or retail
HB336 INTRODUCED
225 sales tax rate on food for local sales and use taxes. The
226 ordinance or resolution must be adopted at least 60 days prior
227 to becoming effective and shall take effect on October 1
228 following adoption.
229 (c) A county or municipal governing body that reduces
230 its general or retail sales tax rate on food for local sales
231 and use taxes pursuant to this section may subsequently
232 increase the rate on food not to exceed the rate in effect in
233 the county or municipality on June 15, 2023, unless otherwise
234 provided by law.
235 (d) Any county or municipal governing body may exempt
236 the gross proceeds from the sale of food from county or
237 municipal sales and use taxes in accordance with Section
238 40-23-4.01."
